deshow/17_lci_campus_bcn_circular_studio_salva_lopez_yatzer.jpg\" src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/17_lci_campus_bcn_circular_studio_salva_lopez_yatzer.jpg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1707\" alt=\"Photography by Salva Lopez.\" title=\"Photography by Salva Lopez.\" data-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/17_lci_campus_bcn_circular_studio_salva_lopez_yatzer.jpg\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\n\n  \n      \u003cp\u003ePhotography by Salva Lopez.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n  \u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n  \n  \n\n\n  \n  \u003cfigure\u003e\n    \u003cimg data-original-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/18_lci_campus_bcn_circular_studio_pedro_noguera_yatzer.jpg\" src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/18_lci_campus_bcn_circular_studio_pedro_noguera_yatzer.jpg\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1845\" alt=\"Photography by Pedro Noguera.\" title=\"Photography by Pedro Noguera.\" data-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/18_lci_campus_bcn_circular_studio_pedro_noguera_yatzer.jpg\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\n\n  \n      \u003cp\u003ePhotography by Pedro Noguera.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n  \u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n  \n  \n\n\n  \n  \u003cfigure\u003e\n    \u003cimg data-original-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/28_lci_campus_bcn_circular_studio_pedro_noguera_yatzer.jpg\" src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/28_lci_campus_bcn_circular_studio_pedro_noguera_yatzer.jpg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1806\" alt=\"Photography by Pedro Noguera.\" title=\"Photography by Pedro Noguera.\" data-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/28_lci_campus_bcn_circular_studio_pedro_noguera_yatzer.jpg\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\n\n  \n      \u003cp\u003ePhotography by Pedro Noguera.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n  \u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n    \u003cp\u003eWhen it comes to the building\u0026#39;s circulation, this has been cleverly organized around its perimeter, turning passageways into multifunctional areas that act as social zones, workspaces, and exhibition spaces, an approach that redefines the conventional use of hallways, transforming them into vibrant spaces for interaction, sharing ideas, and showcasing work. \u003cstrong\u003eFrom the third to the fifth floors, the building’s circulation extends externally, with pathways that overlook the surrounding cityscape as well as views of the sea. \u003c/strong\u003eBetween the third and the fifth floors, an elevated \u0026#34;raised plaza\u0026#34; on the fourth floor serves as the focal point of the building, in the form of an outdoor space that is sheltered from direct sunlight, where students can gather, study, or take a break, enjoying the Mediterranean breeze.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThroughout, \u003cstrong\u003esustainable design elements have earned the campus BREEAM certification, highlighting its energy-efficient architecture and alignment with global standards in environmental responsibility, in a nod to LCI Education\u0026#39;s Canadian roots. \u003c/strong\u003eHowever you look at it, LCI Barcelona\u0026#39;s new campus stands as a bold vision of modern education, where architecture, learning, and urban life seamlessly converge to create a dynamic ecosystem that adapts to the needs of its diverse student community, ultimately setting a new standard for creative learning environments.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n  \n  